The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Tuesday, April 13, 2004  Good Morning Hello It's Tuesday, April 13, 2004				 																Road to avoid				 																																	Traffic diversions are likely around Kalighat temple to cope with a rush of devotees for Poila Baisakh rituals.				 																Soiree				 																																	An evening of adda and music, organised by Karaoke Juke Box, at Lake Club, 7 pm onwards.				 																Theatre 				 																																	Rani Rashmoni will be staged by Calcutta Club at Kala Mandir, 6.30 pm, to mark the Bengali new year.				 																Dance				 																																	Vasundhara, a programme of folk dances to mark Vishuba Sankranti, organised by Eastern Zonal Cultural Centre, at Bharatiyam, at 6.30 pm.				 																Exhibitions				 																																	An exhibition of paintings, installations, caricature, graffiti and other media works on Vote, to whom dost thou belong? at CIMA Gallery, 2 pm-7 pm.				 																																	An exhibition of innovative Indian products at Calcutta Ice Skating Rink, from 10 am to 8 pm.				 																																	A range of casualwear and other accessories on display at Sasha, on Mirza Ghalib Street.
